u2019m assuming that the .debs should conflict if they install a common file. Does it make sense to allow side-by-side installations here?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>But then we won\u2019t be able to use the previous version, right? And I\u2019m assuming that the .debs should conflict if they install a common file. Does it make sense to allow side-by-side installations here?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-05-13T23:01:58.825683+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Carlos Ag\u00fcero", "uuid": "{da8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bda8a8e89-4bb0-421b-bd0e-dbbed3d4ed6a%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/692bf15758111acaddae4da15a47f9e5d=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsCA-0.png"}}, "nickname": "caguero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:4ded1ddf-947e-4154-bbd1-3dba24f1bdbd"}, "updated_on": "2019-05-13T23:01:58.835097+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 101863851}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pullrequests/15/comments/101864305.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pull-requests/15/_/diff#comment-101864305"}}, "parent": {"id": 101863851, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pullrequests/15/comments/101863851.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pull-requests/15/_/diff#comment-101863851"}}, "depth": 4}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 15, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pullrequests/15.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pull-requests/15"}}, "title": "Merge forward from ign-tools0 and bump to 1.0.0"}, "content": {"raw": "> But then we won\u2019t be able to use the previous version, right?\n\nI think then we'd need to use the full executable path", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<blockquote>\n<p>But then we won\u2019t be able to use the previous version, right?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think then we'd need to use the full executable path</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-05-13T23:10:21.052347+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d2479544ec4%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8/7d903d90-c5ea-4182-b7ef-0d467e9e1c74/128"}}, "nickname": "chapulina", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:6ff86fcb-b7ab-44a5-b8a6-f6d9cae8b6e8"}, "updated_on": "2019-05-13T23:10:21.061941+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 101864305}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pullrequests/15/comments/102206667.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pull-requests/15/_/diff#comment-102206667"}}, "parent": {"id": 101863851, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pullrequests/15/comments/101863851.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pull-requests/15/_/diff#comment-101863851"}}, "depth": 4}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 15, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pullrequests/15.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-tools/pull-requests/15"}}, "title": "Merge forward from ign-tools0 and bump to 1.0.0"}, "content": {"raw": "If we want to have a single command \\(\\`ign\\`\\) that can work as a wrapper to call a given version of ign-tools then we have different options:\n\n1. Add the logic to do this in the ign command \\(modify the code in this repo\\)\n2. Leave the code as it is now and drop the responsibility of handling different versions under the same command to the packaging system:\n\n    1. Ubuntu/Debian uses `update-alternatives`\n    2. Don\u2019t know how brew or windows will handle this.\n    \n\nIn the short term we can make the packages to conflict and do not support side-by-side installations if it is not a critical use case.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>If we want to have a single command (`ign`) that can work as a wrapper to call a given version of ign-tools then we have different options:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Add the logic to do this in the ign command (modify the code in this repo)</li>\n<li>\n<p>Leave the code as it is now and drop the responsibility of handling different versions under the same command to the packaging system:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Ubuntu/Debian uses <code>update-alternatives</code></li>\n<li>Don\u2019t know how brew or windows will handle this.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>In the short term we can make the packages to conflict and do not support side-by-side installations if it is not a critical use case.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-05-15T21:53:00.005848+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJR-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Jose Luis Rivero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:155a32e2-420c-4d50-98e0-0e722f63f906"}, "updated_on": "2019-05-15T21:53:00.015764+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 102206667}], "page": 1, "size": 11}